wiki_section_text: Brownsville is the fourth largest city in South Texas .

intro: South Texas is a region of the U.S. state of Texas that lies roughly south of - and including - San Antonio. The southern and western boundary is the Rio Grande, and to the east it is the Gulf of Mexico. The population of this region is about 4.96 million according to the 2017 census estimates. The southern portion of this region is often referred to as the Rio Grande Valley. The eastern portion along the Gulf of Mexico is also referred to as the Coastal Bend.
